{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_55","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc 'nl -ba .vault/plan.md'","aggregated_output":"     1\t# MiniLang LSP Plan\n     2\t\n     3\t## Priority Rules (must hold)\n     4\t1. `encodeMessage` must emit valid LSP JSON-RPC envelopes with `Content-Length`, blank line separator, and exact message body bytes (`framed.length === headerLen + bodyLen`).\n     5\t2. `MessageBuffer.push()` must buffer partial chunks, decode one or more complete messages, and never emit partial/incomplete payloads.\n     6\t3. `initialize` must return `textDocumentSync`, `completionProvider`, `definitionProvider`, `hoverProvider`; `shutdown` must return `{result:null}` and `exit` must return `null`.\n     7\t4. `didOpen` and `didChange` must publish diagnostics through `textDocument/publishDiagnostics` notifications and persist per-URI diagnostics via `getDiagnostics(uri)`.\n     8\t5. Diagnostics must detect undefined symbols and function-arity mismatches; diagnostics set must replace old results so stale issues are cleared on later updates.\n     9\t6. Parser must support syntax/brace recovery: malformed input (missing `}`) may emit syntax diagnostics but must still produce and preserve semantic diagnostics when possible.\n    10\t7. Completion must filter by cursor prefix and lexical scope, include MiniLang keywords, symbols in scope, and function signature items/snippets suitable for insertion.\n    11\t8. `textDocument/definition` must locate the correct symbol target, preferring inner/local symbol scope over outer/global same-name symbols.\n    12\t9. `textDocument/hover` must return function/symbol details (at minimum signature/name and context-appropriate docs).\n    13\t\n    14\t## Build Checklist\n    15\t- Parse/implement `parseMiniLang` as source of truth for symbols + diagnostics.\n    16\t- Implement LSP message routing for requests, notifications, and diagnostics queue.\n    17\t- Add document versioned storage and incremental change handling.\n    18\t- Add focused regression tests for stale-diagnostic clearing, scope shadowing, and brace-recovery behavior.\n    19\t- Run: `npm test` and confirm all `test/lsp.visible.test.mjs` cases pass.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
